event,"

Last night at the Anchor show...While Blood Comes Ashore was playing, Tony from xSaintsneversurrenderx came up to me and was like, ""Do you own a white cutlass sierra?"" And I said, ""No, it's a buick century."" And he said, ""Yeah, with a bunch of stickers, right?"" And I said, ""Yeah, why?"" And then he said, ""Well it's been hit."" And I said, ""What do you mean it's been hit?"" And he's like ""Some guy in a truck hit it, he's out there now."" And I was like, ""How bad?"" And he said, ""Really bad."" And then I ran outside with Tony, Matisse, and Sarah Leavell on my heels. I ran up to my car and threw a huge fit. I started cussing and screaming and kicking my car then burst into tears because this car meant more to me than most people on this planet. I called my mom and she and Jim Miller came out, and we all talked to the cop that came. I guess the guy fell asleep at the wheel and barreled right into the back of my car, drove off, and came back later because he felt bad or something. I don't know anything for sure, but I sure hope I get a good car out of this. I won't say ""BETTER"" because NO FUCKING CAR BEAT MY BABY. <
And after they took my baby away, Matisse, Brandon and I went to Ihop. Brandon paid <
Some things aren't always how they appear to be.
I'll just show you how fucking ugly I can be."
event,"Recall a memory from every age you've lived to see:
3-I woke up from a bad dream and started screaming because I was alone in my parents room and it was really dark.
4-Lots of imaginary friends, my little ponies, and adventures with my older sister, Sarah.
5-My sister randomly ran up to me, pushed me off a swing and it knocked the air out of me.
6-Having my lucky marble taken from me and screaming at the whole class.
7-Starting school without any previous experience with kids of my own age.
8-In school detention for being out of dress code.
9-Having to pee my pants because the teacher wouldn't let me use the restroom.
10-Had a horrible teacher who was obsessed with the Colts. (Must've turned me off of sports forever).
11-First time I heard the Spice Girls. hahahha
12-Didn't have a single friend or person to talk to (But, eventually met the only person who has remained my friend for this long)
18-Maintained my wonderful taste in style, music, and people."

Worked on Friday. Was visited by a fellow FWM board member. Saw a movie. Went to Matisse's.
Woke up at Matisse's. Stopped by B-rock's for a bit. Saw a few bands at a Huntington local show.
Came home bored. Stayed home bored."

event,"I bought some Cure and Bjork CD's to celebrate the season change. Yesterday was a mix of pretty cool and really fucking shitty. I got pissed off too many times. Some people really are true bastards. No, xtiffanyx, I'm not talking about you. I'm gonna try to get a job at one of the Munchie's. Maybe I could handle the two job thing. I certainly have some spare time I'd like to kill that I've been wasting lately. It's so fucking pretty outside. Sometimes I lose my appreciation for what nature can do...but when it's rainy autumn...I just feel fucking great. Well..right now I don't, and I'm gonna try and fix that. Movie tonight with the cxc's then to Matisse's I believe. I'm gonna work on my art project all day and listen to my CD's...so if you wanna call me before say...8 PM, do so. 260 356 3762.

event,"""I just want to make a clean escape. I'm leaving but I don't know where to.""
The informal goodbye of an online farewell.
Damien = It's been so much fucking fun, the few times we've actually hung out and spoken. I wish you the best.
Alex = You're better off away from this place, I hope you achieve all the fun you've been searching for. I WILL miss you.
Nolan = I'm not sure when or where you will be going anymore, the plan keeps changing, I hope you pick the right place.
Clinton = It's so neat seeing you back in town, but Germany must be so much cooler. I can't wait until you're back for a longer amount of time.
Matisse = You don't leave for a few months, and you won't be far off, but you're the coolest fucking girl, and I'll miss our weekend shenanigans.
God, who else is leaving so I can write you a formal goodbye?"
